{"tid":1673869,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"彭斯對香港發言全文出爐「支持香港繼續非暴力示威」","createTime":"2019-10-25T01:46:51.000Z","updateTime":"2019-10-25T06:34:00.000Z","uid":73915,"like":16,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":26,"replies":[{"pid":"d9b395a4c733eb81a252489b5b0103cbc2fdacc7","tid":1673869,"uid":73915,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:46:51.000Z","msg":"過去幾個月「幾百萬非暴力示威」既香港人，美國支持你們<br />\n支持大家「繼續非暴力」示威<br />\n<br />\n火魔裝修獅鳥都叫非暴力<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n自己睇全文啦<br />\n<br />\nBut nothing in the past year has put on display the Chinese Communist Party&rsquo;s antipathy to liberty so much as the unrest in Hong Kong.<br />\n<br />\nAnd as millions have taken to the streets in peaceful protest, we&rsquo;ve spoken out on behalf of the people of Hong Kong.  And President Trump has made it clear from early on that <span style=\"color: red;\">there must be a peaceful resolution that respects the rights of the people of Hong Kong, as outlined in the 1984 Sino-British Joint Declaration.</span><br />\n<br />\n...<br />\n<br />\nHong Kong has served as an important gateway between China and the wider world for 150 years.  Hong Kong is one of the freest economies in the world, with strong, independent legal institutions and a lively free press, and it&rsquo;s home to hundreds of thousands of foreign residents.<br />\n<br />\nHong Kong is a living example of what can happen when China embraces liberty.  And yet, for the last few years, Beijing has increased its interventions in Hong Kong and engaged in actions to curtail the rights and liberties of its people &mdash; rights and liberties that were guaranteed through a binding international agreement of &ldquo;one country, two systems.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nBut President Trump has been clear, as he said in his words, <span style=\"color: red;\">&ldquo;The United States stands for liberty.&rdquo;</span>  (Applause.)  We respect the sovereignty of nations.  But America expects Beijing to honor its commitments, and President Trump has repeatedly made it clear <span style=\"color: red;\">it would be much harder for us to make a trade deal if the authorities resort to the use of violence against protestors in Hong Kong.</span>  (Applause.)<br />\n<br />\nSince then, I&rsquo;m pleased to observe that Hong Kong authorities have withdrawn the extradition bill that sparked the protests in the first place, and Beijing has shown some restraint.<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">In the days ahead, I can assure you, the United States will continue to urge China to show restraint, to honor its commitments, and respect the people of Hong Kong.  And to the millions in Hong Kong who have been peacefully demonstrating to protect your rights these past months, we stand with you.  (Applause.)  We are inspired by you, and we urge you to stay on the path of nonviolent protest.  (Applause.)  But know that you have the prayers and the admiration of millions of Americans.</span>"},{"pid":"7af949039a5c17b01e1541be4ce8e2b3a980d499","tid":1673869,"uid":73915,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:46:59.000Z","msg":"...<br />\n<br />\nNike promotes itself as a so called &ldquo;social justice champion,&rdquo; but when it comes to Hong Kong, it prefers checking its social conscience at the door.  Nike stores in China actually removed their Houston Rockets merchandise from their shelves to join the Chinese government in protest against the Rockets general manager&rsquo;s <span style=\"color: red;\">seven-word tweet, which read: &ldquo;Fight for Freedom.  Stand with Hong Kong.&rdquo;</span><br />\n<br />\n...<br />\n<br />\nAll that Beijing is doing today, from the Party&rsquo;s great firewall in cyberspace or to that great wall of sand in the South China Sea, <span style=\"color: red;\">from their distrust of Hong Kong&rsquo;s autonomy</span>, or their repression of people of faith all demonstrate that it&rsquo;s the Chinese Communist Party that has been &ldquo;de-coupling&rdquo; from the wider world for decades."},{"pid":"9538b32da62cf8fd4ddb872677fd8c140e2f69b2","tid":1673869,"uid":48083,"like":1,"dislike":2,"score":-1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:48:56.000Z","msg":"人哋扮睇唔到啫"},{"pid":"f17135a3d09425f53df5ddff497d9576bb39c178","tid":1673869,"uid":256142,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:49:18.000Z","msg":"(for TLDR...)<br />\n牙彭: 核爆都唔割"},{"pid":"c20f5fa20672ae771c8408f167acc041434c2d1b","tid":1673869,"uid":279356,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:50:48.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/cW22zhe.gif\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FcW22zhe.gif&h=aee66c3f&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"b7c02469932e9b379c5900dd03202b4869bb1c5e","tid":1673869,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:52:23.000Z","msg":"幫樓主補source<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.hkcnews.com/article/24427/彭斯-中美關係-24427/彭斯演說中文翻譯全文\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hkcnews.com%2Farticle%2F24427%2F%E5%BD%AD%E6%96%AF-%E4%B8%AD%E7%BE%8E%E9%97%9C%E4%BF%82-24427%2F%E5%BD%AD%E6%96%AF%E6%BC%94%E8%AA%AA%E4%B8%AD%E6%96%87%E7%BF%BB%E8%AD%AF%E5%85%A8%E6%96%87&d=wRNUG5%2F8jzvhtT%2FDMFjpNkYzBSotcsoJ75UENuGtOl4%3D&h=c2a6cf07\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.hkcnews.com/article/24427/彭斯-中美關係-24427/彭斯演說中文翻譯全文</a>"},{"pid":"b7a9c8c4628067ebdcf97553b845ff54c1f2b4c8","tid":1673869,"uid":249263,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-25T01:53:04.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://twitter.com/reuters/status/1187436338368450560?s=21\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Freuters%2Fstatus%2F1187436338368450560%3Fs%3D21&d=wRNUG5%2F8jzvhtT%2FDMFjpNkYzBSotcsoJ75UENuGt